description: For this group of gorgeous teens, New York is all about parties, fashion - and blood. Schuyler Van Alen is a loner and happy that way. But when she turns fifteen, her life dramatically changes. A mosaic of blue veins appears on her arms, and she begins to have memories of another time and place. When a classmate is found dead at a night club, the mystery deepens. Most surprising of all, Jack Force, the hottest boy in school, starts showing a sudden interest in her. Schuyler wants answers, but is she prepared to learn the truth, especially when she discovers her part in it? Available in Softcover and Hardcover editions.
name: HC

description: Originally from the pages of Weird Tales magazine, here collected are all 16 stories and 2 novels of the detective, scholar, and playboy-investigator of supernatural events. Armed with an unparalleled knowledge of the occult-and his magic sword-cane-he takes on vampires, werewolves, and the enigmatic shonokins, creatures who ruled before the dawn of man.
name: HC

description: Captain America, Thor, and Iron Man each face a different adversary only to conclude in the Quinjet later on that each of the enemies they fought had inter-connected parts in a greater elaborate and diabolical plan. They contemplate on the list of enemies they have fought over the years before coming to land before an American Armed Forces Exchange declaring that the true heroes of this day and age are members of the U.S. military.
name: New Avengers: X Exchange

description: Another collection of the best and brightest of holiday-themed Gold Digger work from creator Fred Perry! Celebrate anytime of year you like with the Diggers sisters and their friends and family!
name: Tanya's Wonderful Life; Night of the Gobs; Is This the Year Without A Daddy-Claus?

description: With the damage done by the gang of hooligans to the town's fence, a tide of death and destruction is unleashed on Marshville! Meriem must now help stem the advance of dozens of starving carnivores. Inundating the streets, they attack and eat anything that moves or doesn't move for that matter! Cavewoman must go on the offensive to once again try to save the day!

After mounting a successful counter attack against the ravenous onslaught of bloodthirsty carnivores, Meriem receives a note. The gang that damaged the fence and let the creatures into town have now kidnapped Bruce. They are blaming her for interfering and demand she leave the town of Marshville forever, or Bruce will die.
Translates Ultimate Comics Spider-Man #14, Ultimate Comics X-Men #15 & Ultimate Comics Ultimates #14-15.
name: Divididos, caemos Segunda Parte

description:
DEATH OF THE FAMILY continues! Batman heads into his showdown with The Joker as the madmans plan is finally revealed in Arkham Asylum! It all leads into next months terrifying conclusion!

And in the backup story, in the midst of The Jokers assault on Batman and his allies, get a secret glimpse into what started The Crown Prince of Crime on his horrifying journey!
name: Castle of Cards; Judgement

description: The Man of Steel's at a happy point in his life--he's got some good news to share with Batman. But tragic times are just around the corner, as one of Batman's deadliest foes is in Metropolis on a surprise visit!
name: Chapter 1

description:
The first time in print for these digital-first stories based on the hit video game Batman: Arkham City.

The Penguin recruits Deadshot to end his rivalry with The Joker!

The origin of Deadshot is revealed!
name: Operation: Kill Joker

description:
Welcome new series writer Michael Alan Nelson (Fall of Cthulhu, 28 Days Later)!

Rose Wilson and Warblade are hunting a rogue Ravager when it accidentally infects an entire community!

What happens here will affect their future with the Colony forever!
name: Pray That Ye May Be Healed!

description:
Part Lost, Part Island of Dr. Moreau and part Jungle Book, Sanctuary is a comic book series by Stephen Coughlin. A mysterious research station on a secluded island houses a game reserve/sanctuary where the animals seem to be just a tad smarter than the human researchers observing them. The arrival of a Panda bear threatens to upset the delicate balance of life for everyone involved. Sanctuary has a cute and amusing exterior which surrounds a dark and deep adventure.

Behind all of the cuteness lurks something slightly mysterious and just a little bit creepy. This is the best way to describe the new digital comic book series Sanctuary by Stephen Coughlin. A research station on a secluded island houses a game reserve/sanctuary where the animals seem to be just a tad smarter than the human researchers observing them. The arrival of a Panda bear threatens to upset the delicate balance of life for everyone involved.
name: Fresh Meat

description: The second issue of Stephen Coughlin's new digital comic book series Sanctuary drives us deeper into mysteries and questions. The death of one of the research stations inhabitants opens up an investigation from both the human and animal inhabitants of the island while the humans make a shocking discovery about one of their animals.
name: Fresh Meat II

description:
One of the island's human researchers gets into trouble with his bosses as the tigers press their own investigation of the death of the panda.

Plus, talking gorillas and, well, a big shock at the end.
name: Fresh Meat III

description: The penultimate issue of Stephen Coughlin's Sanctuary arrives and finds us on the cusp of both new discoveries and big revelations about the island habitat and the people and creatures that inhabit it.
name: Fresh Meat IV

description: Lies, murder, escape, and exploding squirrels! Chaos reigns in the sanctuary as more secrets are revealed!
name: Fresh Meat V

person_credits.name: Mary Fleener
person_credits.role: writer, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

description: Critically acclaimed cartoonist Brahm Revel continues his tale of primate military prowess! Private John Francis Clayton's strange tour of duty in Vietnam gets stranger as he struggles with the unbelievable facts he is faced with. The elite platoon of simian soldiers he's encountered don't make any more sense to him than the war he's been sent to fight, but is this squad of chain-smoking chimps the most dangerous force in the jungle or are they merely a distraction from the larger evil growing in the wild?
name: Volume 2

description:
Tokyo Zombie is a horror-comedy manga about two blue-collar factory workers (who happen to be jiu-jitsu experts) dealing with a zombie uprising in Tokyo.

When the story begins, Fujio and Mitsuo are dreaming of training in martial arts overseas and becoming famous. When they accidentally kill their overbearing boss, they decide to cover up the evidence and bury him at a man-made garbage mountain known as DARK FUJI. Unfortunately for them, the tons of rotting garbage have been contaminated with industrial waste... Which, naturally, transforms the bodies of the dead into ravenous, flesh-eating zombies.

Fuji and Mitsuo try their best to survive in this horrific new landscape, but the hapless pair become separated after an idiotic mistake involving potato chips and a stray dog.

Skip to a few years later. Post-apocalyptic Tokyo has become a feudalistic society, in which the rich have enslaved the lower classes, who toil in the walled city for protection against the zombies. To alleviate boredom, the rich have created gladiator death matches, pitting zombies against slaves. Fuji and Mitsuo meet up under strange circumstances in the ring of one of these death matches. All hell breaks loose when the two are reunited, and the sanctuary city of the rich comes under fire from a revolutionary pig farmer and a motorcycle gang of roving bandits.

Tokyo Zombie was originally serialized in the cutting-edge manga magazine AX from 1998 to 1999. Many years before the film Shaun of the Dead introduced Western audiences to the zombie comedy genre, Hanakuma's send up of Romero zombie films and post-apocalyptic survival story was already a cult classic in Japan. Now English-speaking audiences will have the chance to check out the genre-mashing tale that started it all.

Hanakuma's "heta uma" (Literally "Bad, but Good") drawing style punctuates the gory but hilarious depiction of a Tokyo overrun with zombies. This is mixed with a dynamic and authentic depiction of actual martial arts, sourced from Hanakuma's own years of training and competing as a professional martial artist. In addition to the success of the cult manga, Tokyo Zombie was also adapted into a hit film directed by Sakichi Sato and starring cult film stars Tadanobu Asano (Ichi the Killer) and Sho Aikawa (Dead or Alive), with a cameo from famed horror manga artist Kazuo Umezu.
name: Vol. 1

person_credits.name: Jack T. Chick
person_credits.role: writer, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

description:
Is your mom a zombie? Sis? Dad?! Who you gonna call? Savage Brothers!

Have an undead loved one that needs retrieving? Call Dale and Otis Savage--they'll hop in their Ford F-150, bring'em back, or put 'em down. But when they get hired to retrieve a zombie scientist who holds the key to the supernatural apocalypse--are they selling out the human race? And when did the Savage Brothers start making bid decisions like this? And who is the mysterious guy with no body they call...The Head!?!? Anybody got some more barbecue.

Bonus: FEAR THE DEAD - Michael Alan Nelson's complete guidebook to the wondrous world of the undead, as seen through the eyes of one survivor of the Zombie Apocalypse! Featuring art from tons of today's terror titans!
name: TPB

description: In the heart of the African wilderness, a safari guide is witness to the grisly murder of a fellow guide by a gorilla. In order to make sense of this horrifying experience, he sets out to find out why.
